f) The traditional graph, 教, with a cross rather than 土 in the upper right, is 
etymologically correct. The simplified form makes an historically false, but 
mnemonically useful identification with 孝 xiào ‘to be filial’. However, in its 
original form, the graph is said to show 爻 yáo and a child, plus the radical on the 
right called fǎnwénr or or fǎnwénpáng, ‘back-to-front wén’  (presumably because 
